WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-US

00:00:02.633 --> 00:00:04.500
Why do you need to control oil for oily skin?

00:00:04.500 --> 00:00:05.733
If you don't control

00:00:05.833 --> 00:00:08.033
oil, the oil you produce will oxidize and turn yellow,

00:00:08.033 --> 00:00:11.033
making your face look like it's covered with a layer of soy sauce.

00:00:11.200 --> 00:00:12.466
If you don't control

00:00:12.466 --> 00:00:15.666
oil, the oil you produce will oxidize to form peroxides, 

00:00:15.666 --> 00:00:17.066
which will irritate your skin

00:00:17.066 --> 00:00:18.033
and cause you to break out.

00:00:18.200 --> 00:00:19.333
If you don't control oil,

00:00:19.333 --> 00:00:20.633
then

00:00:20.633 --> 00:00:22.833
the sunscreen film may be destroyed,

00:00:22.833 --> 00:00:26.066
and your delicate makeup may collapse due to oil production.

00:00:26.266 --> 00:00:27.933
Therefore,

00:00:27.933 --> 00:00:30.200
oil control is very necessary for oily skin. 

00:00:30.300 --> 00:00:32.533
It is the basis of your daily skin care

00:00:32.533 --> 00:00:35.600
and the key to preventing acne and yellowing.

00:00:35.800 --> 00:00:36.533
But the problem is that

00:00:36.533 --> 00:00:39.900
the oil control methods on the Internet are very fragmented.

00:00:39.900 --> 00:00:41.266
Some people tell you to apply loose powder,

00:00:41.266 --> 00:00:42.500
and some tell you to use acid.

00:00:42.666 --> 00:00:45.133
These methods may not be suitable for you at all,

00:00:45.133 --> 00:00:47.033
causing you to develop closed comedones and allergies.

00:00:47.100 --> 00:00:49.666
They may also work well at the beginning,

00:00:49.666 --> 00:00:51.333
but then they stop working after a while. 

00:00:51.633 --> 00:00:53.233
The reason for these results

00:00:53.233 --> 00:00:56.100
is that these methods are one-sided.

00:00:56.300 --> 00:00:59.022
So today I want to explain 

00:00:59.033 --> 00:01:02.200
to you one thing from a more scientific and systematic perspective,

00:01:02.200 --> 00:01:05.100
that is, how should oily skin control oil?

00:01:12.300 --> 00:01:14.666
First of all, why does the skin produce oil?

00:01:14.666 --> 00:01:18.500
In fact, the oil we produce is not produced by the skin,

00:01:18.500 --> 00:01:22.218
but deep inside the skin. The sebaceous glands

00:01:22.233 --> 00:01:24.000
are located deep inside the pores. 

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:25.333
They secrete oil and then

00:01:25.333 --> 00:01:27.866
transport it to the surface of the skin through the pores.

00:01:27.866 --> 00:01:29.133
This is the oil we secrete.

00:01:29.233 --> 00:01:29.933
Generally speaking,

00:01:29.933 --> 00:01:30.533
these oils

00:01:30.533 --> 00:01:32.266
include triglycerides,

00:01:32.266 --> 00:01:34.066
a small amount of squalene and wax.

00:01:34.066 --> 00:01:35.666
They can help moisturize the skin,

00:01:35.666 --> 00:01:37.066
maintain the integrity of the barrier,

00:01:37.066 --> 00:01:39.633
and prevent the moisture in the skin from being lost easily.

00:01:39.800 --> 00:01:42.000
But when it is secreted too much,

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:42.900
it is not good

00:01:42.900 --> 00:01:44.733
because it will clog the pores.

00:01:44.900 --> 00:01:47.100
The peroxides formed after oxidation

00:01:47.100 --> 00:01:48.300
will also irritate the skin and

00:01:48.300 --> 00:01:49.233
cause you to get acne

00:01:49.233 --> 00:01:51.733
. So the key to oily skin care

00:01:51.733 --> 00:01:54.466
is to regulate

00:01:54.466 --> 00:01:56.033
the secretion of oil by the sebaceous glands

00:01:56.200 --> 00:01:59.100
. What are the factors that affect the secretion of sebaceous glands?

00:01:59.100 --> 00:02:02.000
They include age factors, endocrine factors,

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:03.233
hormonal factors

00:02:03.266 --> 00:02:04.800
, body temperature,

00:02:04.800 --> 00:02:05.866
external temperature

00:02:05.866 --> 00:02:07.633
, the integrity of your barrier

00:02:07.633 --> 00:02:10.533
, and factors affected by various external stimuli.

00:02:10.533 --> 00:02:12.233
We divide these factors

00:02:12.233 --> 00:02:13.866
into two types.

00:02:13.866 --> 00:02:16.200
One is like hormones and endocrines, which

00:02:16.200 --> 00:02:17.633
belong to internal factors

00:02:17.666 --> 00:02:20.400
, which are determined by our own body.

00:02:20.500 --> 00:02:21.466
The other part is

00:02:21.466 --> 00:02:23.100
like the degree of damage to your barrier

00:02:23.100 --> 00:02:23.900
, temperature

00:02:23.900 --> 00:02:26.733
, and the stimulation caused by using some products. This

00:02:26.866 --> 00:02:28.266
is called external factors

00:02:28.266 --> 00:02:31.300
. If it is determined by these external conditions,

00:02:31.333 --> 00:02:33.633
then if you want a scientific and

00:02:33.633 --> 00:02:35.133
systematic method of oil control

00:02:35.133 --> 00:02:38.600
, you must regulate both internal and external factors. Let's talk

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:43.200
about the

00:02:43.200 --> 00:02:45.000
two main influencing factors of internal factors

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:46.300
. One is the hormonal factor

00:02:46.300 --> 00:02:47.866
and the other is the endocrine factor

00:02:47.966 --> 00:02:49.200
. As for the hormonal factor,

00:02:49.200 --> 00:02:52.200
in fact, its core influence on our oil production

00:02:52.200 --> 00:02:53.333
is androgen.

00:02:53.466 --> 00:02:56.900
Androgen can make the secretion of sebaceous glands become active,

00:02:57.000 --> 00:03:00.666
which is why men generally have oilier skin than women.

00:03:00.700 --> 00:03:02.000
But the hormonal factor

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:04.233
is difficult to be affected by our daily diet

00:03:04.233 --> 00:03:05.866
and external skin care products.

00:03:05.933 --> 00:03:07.233
So for the internal factors,

00:03:07.233 --> 00:03:10.033
our focus is on endocrine regulation. How do

00:03:10.266 --> 00:03:11.466
endocrine changes

00:03:11.466 --> 00:03:14.333
control the sebaceous glands to secrete oil?

00:03:14.466 --> 00:03:16.633
There is such a physiological pathway in the body.

00:03:16.833 --> 00:03:18.533
When your blood sugar rises,

00:03:18.533 --> 00:03:20.833
it will promote your body to secrete insulin

00:03:20.866 --> 00:03:21.866
, and insulin

00:03:21.866 --> 00:03:24.533
will promote the secretion of insulin growth factor

00:03:24.533 --> 00:03:26.033
. This growth factor

00:03:26.033 --> 00:03:28.700
can increase the activity of sebaceous glands in secreting oil.

00:03:28.700 --> 00:03:31.666
So these processes in the middle are ignored

00:03:31.666 --> 00:03:34.933
. In short, the faster

00:03:34.933 --> 00:03:36.400
and more violently

00:03:36.400 --> 00:03:38.666
your blood sugar rises,

00:03:38.933 --> 00:03:41.500
the more oil your sebaceous glands secrete. The more

00:03:41.500 --> 00:03:45.000
you eat, the more important it is to control oil levels

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:47.600
by regulating your endocrine system.

00:03:47.600 --> 00:03:50.933
This means that you should avoid high-sugar and high-glycemic foods

00:03:51.166 --> 00:03:51.866
when you eat.

00:03:51.866 --> 00:03:53.266
High sugar, as the name

00:03:53.266 --> 00:03:57.300
suggests,

00:03:57.333 --> 00:03:59.533
means high sugar content.

00:03:59.533 --> 00:04:01.100
As you know, many fruits and

00:04:01.100 --> 00:04:02.833
sweets are high-sugar foods. What is high glycemic?

00:04:02.833 --> 00:04:04.733
It means that when you eat this food,

00:04:04.866 --> 00:04:07.500
your blood sugar

00:04:07.500 --> 00:04:10.200
rises to what extent and at what speed.

00:04:10.466 --> 00:04:13.700
This is not necessarily completely consistent with high sugar.

00:04:13.866 --> 00:04:16.400
For example, fruits like apples

00:04:16.400 --> 00:04:17.666
are high in sugar

00:04:17.666 --> 00:04:19.333
but low in glycemic levels, so

00:04:19.400 --> 00:04:20.400
you may eat

00:04:20.400 --> 00:04:22.133
this type of fruit moderately.

00:04:22.200 --> 00:04:24.600
What are high-glycemic foods?

00:04:24.600 --> 00:04:26.900
Typical examples are

00:04:27.033 --> 00:04:29.466
snacks and sweets like milk tea, cakes, etc.

00:04:29.466 --> 00:04:31.400
Also, foods like white rice

00:04:31.466 --> 00:04:32.500
and mashed potatoes

00:04:32.500 --> 00:04:35.400
are all high-glycemic foods .

00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:37.466
We should try our best to avoid

00:04:37.466 --> 00:04:39.800
eating too much of these foods on a daily basis.

00:04:40.033 --> 00:04:42.700
I'll put a table of these foods on the screen

00:04:42.700 --> 00:04:43.866
for you to remember.

00:04:44.133 --> 00:04:45.466
After talking about what you can't eat,

00:04:45.466 --> 00:04:47.800
let's talk about what you should eat,

00:04:47.800 --> 00:04:50.833
which is foods containing Omega. Omega 3 foods or supplements.

00:04:53.200 --> 00:04:55.666
You may have heard of

00:04:55.666 --> 00:04:57.600
it. It can promote brain development,

00:04:57.600 --> 00:04:58.866
repair the nervous system,

00:04:58.866 --> 00:05:00.700
including regulating blood lipids, etc.

00:05:00.733 --> 00:05:02.900
But what people don’t notice is that

00:05:02.900 --> 00:05:05.433
Omega 3 can also control oil

00:05:05.433 --> 00:05:07.433
by regulating insulin growth factor.

00:05:07.700 --> 00:05:08.433
Omega 3

00:05:08.433 --> 00:05:11.533
is a polyunsaturated fatty acid that the human body needs.

00:05:11.633 --> 00:05:12.933
Why is it necessary

00:05:12.933 --> 00:05:16.266
? Because Omega 3 cannot be synthesized by the body itself.

00:05:16.266 --> 00:05:19.300
You can only take it into the body from the outside.

00:05:19.533 --> 00:05:21.100
Omega 3

00:05:21.100 --> 00:05:24.066
is found in large quantities in deep-sea fish, algae

00:05:24.066 --> 00:05:27.833
, and a small amount of seeds in the oil.

00:05:27.866 --> 00:05:30.666
If you don’t have these foods

00:05:30.666 --> 00:05:31.500
in your daily diet,

00:05:31.500 --> 00:05:34.033
you will easily lack Omega 3.

00:05:34.366 --> 00:05:36.933
A more efficient way to do this

00:05:36.933 --> 00:05:38.700
is to take supplements directly

00:05:38.700 --> 00:05:39.900
, that is, fish oil.

00:05:42.433 --> 00:05:43.933
According to the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations

00:05:43.933 --> 00:05:45.833
and the European Food Safety Authority,

00:05:45.833 --> 00:05:49.033
the daily Omega intake for adults is recommended . The recommended daily intake of omega 3

00:05:49.033 --> 00:05:51.733
is more than 250 mg.

00:05:51.733 --> 00:05:53.533
When choosing supplements, we

00:05:53.533 --> 00:05:55.233
can

00:05:55.233 --> 00:05:57.133
choose the content of your supplements based on

00:05:57.300 --> 00:05:58.466
this standard

00:05:58.466 --> 00:06:00.600
. There are two core types of fish oils on the market

00:06:00.700 --> 00:06:02.533
: RTG and

00:06:02.533 --> 00:06:03.833
EE.

00:06:03.933 --> 00:06:05.733
RTG has newer technology, better

00:06:05.733 --> 00:06:06.700
activity, and

00:06:06.700 --> 00:06:07.666
higher absorption,

00:06:07.666 --> 00:06:10.266
while EE is more classic, stable,

00:06:10.266 --> 00:06:11.333
and has a longer shelf life.

00:06:11.533 --> 00:06:13.133
As for related products,

00:06:13.133 --> 00:06:15.233
typical RTG types on the market

00:06:15.233 --> 00:06:18.000
include some fish oils from the brand NYO 3

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:20.733
and fish oils from the brand WHC,

00:06:20.800 --> 00:06:22.133
while classic EE types

00:06:22.133 --> 00:06:24.500
include Webber nature or Mega gold, etc.

00:06:24.500 --> 00:06:25.933
They all have related products.

00:06:26.333 --> 00:06:27.300
A special reminder:

00:06:27.300 --> 00:06:28.700
if you are pregnant,

00:06:28.700 --> 00:06:32.433
you must choose fish oil that does not contain EPA,

00:06:32.433 --> 00:06:34.333
because EPA, an Omega 3,

00:06:34.333 --> 00:06:36.233
can reduce blood viscosity and

00:06:36.233 --> 00:06:37.633
has the effect of activating blood circulation, which

00:06:37.633 --> 00:06:40.100
poses certain risks for pregnant women.

00:06:40.333 --> 00:06:41.200
In summary,

00:06:41.200 --> 00:06:44.200
solving internal causes means solving endocrine problems,

00:06:44.200 --> 00:06:46.133
and in this core

00:06:46.133 --> 00:06:47.466
physiological pathway of endocrine

00:06:47.466 --> 00:06:49.800
, we must solve the problems of increased blood sugar

00:06:49.800 --> 00:06:52.133
and increased insulin growth factor.

00:06:52.233 --> 00:06:53.066
In simple terms

00:06:53.066 --> 00:06:55.333
, avoid eating high-glycemic foods

00:06:55.333 --> 00:06:57.266
and pay attention to supplementing Omega 3.

00:07:02.066 --> 00:07:03.900
Next, let's talk about external

00:07:03.900 --> 00:07:06.900
factors. The core of external factors is the choice of skin care products.

00:07:06.933 --> 00:07:09.733
There are two key words

00:07:09.733 --> 00:07:11.266
when choosing daily skin care products for oily skin.

00:07:11.300 --> 00:07:13.200
One is to cleanse thoroughly,

00:07:13.300 --> 00:07:15.300
and the other is to reduce oil production.

00:07:15.633 --> 00:07:17.000
First, the key to cleansing thoroughly

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:19.433
is to choose a facial cleanser

00:07:19.433 --> 00:07:20.533
suitable for oily skin.

00:07:20.666 --> 00:07:24.500
The key to choosing a facial cleanser is to choose a surfactant.

00:07:24.533 --> 00:07:27.033
There are many types of surfactants,

00:07:27.033 --> 00:07:28.266
such as soap base

00:07:28.266 --> 00:07:30.600
and SLS. SLES

00:07:30.600 --> 00:07:32.000
includes amino acid surfactants

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:33.000
, betaine surfactants

00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:35.033
, and APG

00:07:35.033 --> 00:07:36.833
.

00:07:36.833 --> 00:07:37.733
You must be confused

00:07:37.733 --> 00:07:40.233
when I mention so many types of surfactants, but you will understand

00:07:40.233 --> 00:07:41.300
if I put them on a graph.

00:07:41.300 --> 00:07:43.600
The horizontal axis of this graph is mildness and

00:07:43.700 --> 00:07:45.466
the vertical axis is cleansing power.

00:07:45.466 --> 00:07:47.600
In fact, it is easy for us to see that

00:07:47.600 --> 00:07:48.700
if we have oily skin

00:07:48.700 --> 00:07:51.800
and want to choose a facial cleanser that has good cleansing power

00:07:51.800 --> 00:07:53.100
and can remove oil

00:07:53.100 --> 00:07:56.333
without damaging the barrier,

00:07:56.333 --> 00:07:58.800
then its surfactants should be

00:07:58.800 --> 00:08:02.000
selected from this area, that is, amino acids, APG and betaine.

00:08:02.266 --> 00:08:04.500
What about facial cleansers containing these surfactants?

00:08:04.500 --> 00:08:05.700
Typical products include

00:08:05.700 --> 00:08:07.700
CeraVe,

00:08:07.700 --> 00:08:09.133
Freeplus,

00:08:09.133 --> 00:08:10.800
Paula's Choice Earth Cleanser,

00:08:10.800 --> 00:08:13.266
and Kiehl's Super Moisture Cleanser,

00:08:13.300 --> 00:08:16.200
which is a complex of these three surfactants.

00:08:16.466 --> 00:08:18.633
One thing we should especially remind you of

00:08:18.633 --> 00:08:20.900
is that the APG surfactant

00:08:20.900 --> 00:08:22.066
does not foam

00:08:22.200 --> 00:08:23.933
, so it is easy to be misunderstood

00:08:23.933 --> 00:08:25.533
as having poor cleansing ability,

00:08:25.533 --> 00:08:26.666
but it is not actually true.

00:08:26.666 --> 00:08:28.000
Its cleansing ability is quite good and it

00:08:28.633 --> 00:08:30.133
solves the problem of cleaning thoroughly

00:08:30.133 --> 00:08:33.033
. Let's talk about daily skin care for oily skin. For

00:08:33.100 --> 00:08:34.666
daily skin care for oily skin,

00:08:34.666 --> 00:08:36.833
we must remember a key word

00:08:36.833 --> 00:08:38.400
, which is simplicity.

00:08:38.666 --> 00:08:40.100
Because for oily skin,

00:08:40.100 --> 00:08:42.000
it is very important for the pores to breathe

00:08:42.000 --> 00:08:43.266
. The more layers you apply

00:08:43.266 --> 00:08:45.233
, the less the pores

00:08:45.333 --> 00:08:46.933
can breathe. If they can't breathe, they will be blocked

00:08:46.933 --> 00:08:49.000
, and then you will get closed comedones and acne.

00:08:49.133 --> 00:08:49.933
So

00:08:49.933 --> 00:08:52.666
, when it comes to skin care for oily skin , we should

00:08:52.666 --> 00:08:54.133
reduce the steps as much as possible.

00:08:54.133 --> 00:08:55.833
Once the toner is

00:08:55.933 --> 00:08:58.200
used up, we don't need to use a face cream

00:08:58.200 --> 00:09:00.800
. There is a special case here . If you have mixed dry skin and

00:09:00.800 --> 00:09:02.866
your face has both oily and dry areas,

00:09:02.866 --> 00:09:03.800
then

00:09:03.800 --> 00:09:05.900
we will use zoning skin care.

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:09.000
Products like face cream that are more moisturizing and sealing

00:09:09.000 --> 00:09:11.600
should only be used on the dry cheek area, and

00:09:11.633 --> 00:09:14.066
we should avoid using them on the oily areas

00:09:14.133 --> 00:09:16.300
. When choosing products, we

00:09:16.300 --> 00:09:19.500
should start with three groups of keywords.

00:09:19.500 --> 00:09:22.500
The first group is products that inhibit oil production,

00:09:22.500 --> 00:09:24.533
such as those containing niacinamide,

00:09:24.533 --> 00:09:26.066
zinc,

00:09:26.066 --> 00:09:27.533
L-carnitine

00:09:27.533 --> 00:09:28.600
, olive

00:09:28.600 --> 00:09:30.066
, or vitamin A.

00:09:30.300 --> 00:09:31.266
Typical products

00:09:31.266 --> 00:09:33.800
include the Ordinary's niacinamide 10%

00:09:33.800 --> 00:09:35.300
and zinc essence,

00:09:35.300 --> 00:09:37.066
like the Ordinary's balance

00:09:37.066 --> 00:09:38.433
clarifying Serum

00:09:38.600 --> 00:09:41.033
, and CeraVe PM oil-control lotion,

00:09:41.033 --> 00:09:42.700
Ouma's olive gel,

00:09:42.700 --> 00:09:44.333
Ola's olive essence

00:09:44.333 --> 00:09:46.600
, and SkinCeuticals' color correcting essence, etc.

00:09:46.833 --> 00:09:49.066
For the second type of pore unclogger,

00:09:49.066 --> 00:09:51.233
we can choose

00:09:51.233 --> 00:09:53.333
essences or toners containing mandelic acid or salicylic acid.

00:09:53.333 --> 00:09:55.033
Typical examples

00:09:55.100 --> 00:09:58.133
include Doctor Wu's mandelic acid water,

00:09:58.133 --> 00:09:59.466
mandelic acid essence

00:09:59.500 --> 00:10:02.233
, and Ruo Meixin's mandelic acid essence

00:10:02.233 --> 00:10:04.400
. Ordinary mandelic acid essence,

00:10:04.400 --> 00:10:07.500
salicylic acid body essence or facial essence

00:10:07.500 --> 00:10:10.066
, as well as Xinsui oil-control toner

00:10:10.066 --> 00:10:12.700
and Paula's Choice salicylic acid essence, etc.

00:10:12.866 --> 00:10:13.600
The third category

00:10:13.600 --> 00:10:15.866
is products that contain ingredients that can help you dissipate heat

00:10:15.866 --> 00:10:19.633
or help you absorb oil.

00:10:19.633 --> 00:10:20.633
Typically,

00:10:20.633 --> 00:10:22.333
for example, some products

00:10:22.333 --> 00:10:24.900
contain alcohol that promotes volatility

00:10:25.033 --> 00:10:27.100
or

00:10:27.100 --> 00:10:30.266
products with cooling agents such as menthol and erythritol,

00:10:30.433 --> 00:10:33.500
such as Kiehl's Men's Vitality Toner

00:10:33.500 --> 00:10:36.233
or Nivea Men's Vitality Essence Water

00:10:36.233 --> 00:10:39.000
, etc. The fastest and most effective way

00:10:39.000 --> 00:10:42.133
to help absorb oil is loose powder,

00:10:42.300 --> 00:10:45.500
typically those loose powders that contain silica in the ingredient list,

00:10:45.500 --> 00:10:48.133
especially those that

00:10:48.133 --> 00:10:51.466
claim in their promotional materials that the silica is hollow silica.

00:10:51.566 --> 00:10:52.833
Hollow silica

00:10:52.833 --> 00:10:54.233
can absorb oil

00:10:54.233 --> 00:10:56.433
and wrap the oil you produce. It

00:10:56.433 --> 00:10:58.666
will not affect the surface of your skin.

00:10:58.933 --> 00:11:01.666
